## Rails

**Detection:** `config.ru` + `Gemfile` with `rails` gem

### Detection Commands

```bash
cat Gemfile | grep "gem 'rails'" 2>/dev/null
ls config.ru 2>/dev/null
```

### CLAUDE.md Sections

```markdown
## Implementation Standards

### Rails 7+ Conventions

- **CoC**: Convention over Configuration (don't configure what Rails expects)
- **DRY**: Don't Repeat Yourself (extract to concerns, helpers, services)
- **RESTful**: Resources for all models; 7 standard actions per controller

### Directory Structure

```
app/
  assets/          # JS, CSS, images
  channels/        # Action Cable channels
  controllers/     # ApplicationController + resource controllers
  helpers/         # View helpers
 /javascript/      # JS packs (Webpacker/Propshaft)
  jobs/            # Active Job classes
  mailers/         # Action Mailer classes
  models/          # ActiveRecord models
  services/        # Service objects (custom)
  views/           # Templates (ERB, Haml, Slim)
config/
  routes.rb        # Route definitions
db/
  migrate/         # Database migrations
  schema.rb        # Schema definition
  seeds.rb         # Seed data
spec/              # RSpec tests
  factories/       # FactoryBot factories
  requests/        # Request specs
  system/          # System/feature specs
```

### MVC Patterns

```ruby
# Models: Business logic + associations + validations
class Post < ApplicationRecord
  belongs_to :author, class_name: 'User', inverse_of: :posts
  has_many :comments, dependent: :destroy
  has_and_belongs_to_many :tags

  validates :title, presence: true, length: { maximum: 255 }
  validates :content, presence: true

  scope :published, -> { where.not(published_at: nil) }
  scope :by_tag, ->(tag) { joins(:tags).where(tags: { name: tag }) }

  def publish!
    update!(published_at: Time.current)
  end

  private

  def ensure_slug
    self.slug = title.parameterize if slug.blank?
  end
end
```

### Controllers

```ruby
# RESTful controller
class PostsController < ApplicationController
  before_action :set_post, only: [:show, :edit, :update, :destroy]

  # GET /posts
  def index
    @posts = Post.published.includes(:author, :tags)
                 .order(created_at: :desc)
                 .page(params[:page])

    respond_to do |format|
      format.html
      format.json { render json: @posts }
    end
  end

  # GET /posts/:id
  def show
    @post.increment!(:view_count)
  end

  # POST /posts
  def create
    @post = current_user.posts.build(post_params)

    if @post.save
      redirect_to @post, notice: 'Post was successfully created.'
    else
      render :new, status: :unprocessable_entity
    end
  end

  private

  def post_params
    params.require(:post).permit(:title, :content, tag_ids: [])
  end

  def set_post
    @post = Post.friendly.find(params[:id])
  end
end
```

### Concerns Pattern

```ruby
# For shared behavior across models/controllers
module Taggable
  extend ActiveSupport::Concern

  included do
    has_and_belongs_to_many :tags, dependent: :destroy
  end

  def tag_list
    tags.pluck(:name).join(', ')
  end

  def tag_list=(names)
    self.tags = names.split(',').map(&:strip).map do |name|
      Tag.find_or_create_by!(name: name)
    end
  end
end

# Usage
class Article < ApplicationRecord
  include Taggable
end

class Video < ApplicationRecord
  include Taggable
end
```

### Service Objects

```ruby
# For complex business logic
class PublishPostService
  def initialize(post)
    @post = post
  end

  def call
    Post.transaction do
      @post.publish!
      send_notifications
      update_related_content
    end
  end

  private

  def send_notifications
    @post.subscribers.each do |subscriber|
      PostMailer.with(post: @post, subscriber: subscriber)
                .published.deliver_later
    end
  end
end

# Usage in controller
def publish
  result = PublishPostService.new(@post).call
  redirect_to @post, notice: 'Post published!'
rescue => e
  redirect_to @post, alert: "Failed to publish: #{e.message}"
end
```

### Background Jobs (Sidekiq)

```ruby
class ProcessPostMediaJob
  include Sidekiq::Job

  sidekiq_options retry: 3, dead: true

  def perform(post_id)
    post = Post.find(post_id)
    MediaProcessor.call(post)
  end
end

# Enqueue
ProcessPostMediaJob.perform_async(post.id)
ProcessPostMediaJob.perform_in(1.hour, post.id)
ProcessPostMediaJob.perform_at(2.hours.from_now, post.id)
```

### Build Commands

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `rails server` or `rails s` | Start development server |
| `rails console` or `rails c` | Rails console |
| `rails db:migrate` | Run migrations |
| `rails db:migrate:fresh` | Drop, create, migrate |
| `rails db:migrate:fresh db:seed` | Fresh + seed |
| `rails db:seed` | Seed database |
| `rails db:studio` | Open database GUI |
| `rails routes` | List routes |
| `rails routes -c posts` | Filter by controller |
| `rails test` | Run all tests |
| `rails test:system` | System tests |
| `rspec` | Run RSpec tests |
| `rspec spec/features` | Run feature specs |
| `rubocop` | Run linter |
| `rubocop -A` | Auto-fix linting issues |
| `bundle exec brakeman` | Security scanner |
| `bundle exec bundler-audit` | Gem vulnerability scan |
| `rails credentials:edit` | Edit encrypted credentials |
| `rails runner "Model.count"` | Run Ruby code |

### Common Pitfalls

```markdown
### Pitfalls to Avoid

1. **Fat controllers**: Extract logic to Service Objects
2. **Fat models**: Extract logic to Concerns or Service Objects
3. **N+1 queries**: Always eager load: `includes(:assoc)`
4. **Callbacks in models**: Prefer explicit service methods
5. **Direct SQL**: Use ActiveRecord, then Arel, then raw SQL
6. **Global state in tests**: Use `let`, not instance variables
7. **Skipping migrations**: Never modify migration files after merge
```

