## Flutter

**Detection:** `pubspec.yaml` + `lib/` directory

### Detection Commands

```bash
cat pubspec.yaml | grep "flutter:" 2>/dev/null
ls pubspec.yaml lib/main.dart 2>/dev/null
```

### CLAUDE.md Sections

```markdown
## Implementation Standards

### Flutter 3.19+ Conventions

- **Dart 3.4+**: Null safety required
- **Clean Architecture**: UI → Domain → Data layers
- **Immutable**: Use `final` and immutable data classes
- **Widget-first**: Everything is a widget

### Directory Structure

```
lib/
  main.dart
  app/
    app.dart
    router.dart
  core/
    constants/
    errors/
    utils/
  data/
    datasources/
    models/
    repositories/
  domain/
    entities/
    repositories/
    usecases/
  presentation/
    pages/
    widgets/
    bloc/  # or cubit, provider, riverpod
```

### Clean Architecture Layers

```dart
// domain/entities/post.dart
class Post {
  final String id;
  final String title;
  final String content;
  final DateTime createdAt;

  const Post({
    required this.id,
    required this.title,
    required this.content,
    required this.createdAt,
  });
}

// domain/repositories/post_repository.dart
abstract class PostRepository {
  Future<List<Post>> getPosts();
  Future<Post> getPost(String id);
  Future<Post> createPost(CreatePostParams params);
  Future<void> deletePost(String id);
}

// data/repositories/post_repository_impl.dart
class PostRepositoryImpl implements PostRepository {
  final PostRemoteDataSource remote;
  final PostLocalDataSource local;

  @override
  Future<List<Post>> getPosts() async {
    try {
      final posts = await remote.getPosts();
      local.cachePosts(posts);
      return posts;
    } catch (e) {
      return local.getCachedPosts();
    }
  }
}

// presentation/bloc/post_bloc.dart
class PostBloc extends Bloc<PostEvent, PostState> {
  final GetPosts getPosts;

  PostBloc({required this.getPosts}) : super(PostInitial()) {
    on<LoadPosts>((event, emit) async {
      emit(PostLoading());
      try {
        final posts = await getPosts();
        emit(PostLoaded(posts));
      } catch (e) {
        emit(PostError(e.toString()));
      }
    });
  }
}
```

### Widget Patterns

```dart
// presentation/widgets/post_card.dart
class PostCard extends StatelessWidget {
  final Post post;
  final VoidCallback? onTap;

  const PostCard({
    super.key,
    required this.post,
    this.onTap,
  });

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Card(
      margin: const EdgeInsets.symmetric(horizontal: 16, vertical: 8),
      child: InkWell(
        onTap: onTap,
        borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(12),
        child: Padding(
          padding: const EdgeInsets.all(16),
          child: Column(
            crossAxisAlignment: CrossAxisAlignment.start,
            children: [
              Text(
                post.title,
                style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.titleMedium,
              ),
              const SizedBox(height: 8),
              Text(
                post.content,
                style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.bodyMedium,
                maxLines: 2,
                overflow: TextOverflow.ellipsis,
              ),
            ],
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}
```

### State Management (BLoC Pattern)

```dart
// Using flutter_bloc
import 'package:flutter_bloc/flutter_bloc.dart';

// Events
abstract class PostEvent {}
class LoadPosts extends PostEvent {}
class RefreshPosts extends PostEvent {}

// States
abstract class PostState {}
class PostInitial extends PostState {}
class PostLoading extends PostState {}
class PostLoaded extends PostState {
  final List<Post> posts;
  PostLoaded(this.posts);
}
class PostError extends PostState {
  final String message;
  PostError(this.message);
}

// BLoC
class PostBloc extends Bloc<PostEvent, PostState> {
  final PostRepository repository;

  PostBloc({required this.repository}) : super(PostInitial()) {
    on<LoadPosts>(_onLoadPosts);
    on<RefreshPosts>(_onRefreshPosts);
  }

  Future<void> _onLoadPosts(LoadPosts event, Emitter<PostState> emit) async {
    emit(PostLoading());
    try {
      final posts = await repository.getPosts();
      emit(PostLoaded(posts));
    } catch (e) {
      emit(PostError(e.toString()));
    }
  }
}
```

### Build Commands

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `flutter pub get` | Install dependencies |
| `flutter run` | Run on connected device |
| `flutter run -d <device_id>` | Run on specific device |
| `flutter build apk --debug` | Debug APK |
| `flutter build apk --release` | Release APK |
| `flutter build ios --simulator --no-codesign` | iOS simulator build |
| `flutter build ios --release` | iOS release build |
| `flutter test` | Run widget tests |
| `flutter analyze` | Static analysis |
| `flutter format .` | Format code |
| `flutter pub outdated` | Check for updates |
| `flutter clean` | Clean build artifacts |

### Common Pitfalls

```markdown
### Pitfalls to Avoid

1. **BuildContext in async**: Pass required data explicitly
2. **Memory leaks**: Dispose controllers, streams in dispose()
3. **Rebuild storms**: Use `const` constructors, proper keys
4. **Deeply nested widgets**: Extract to separate widgets
5. **Missing null checks**: Use Dart's null safety fully
```

